@startuml libttak_priority_scheduling
!theme vibrant

title Priority Scheduling

package "Scheduler" {
    [Scheduler] as Sched
    [Nice]
}

package "Priority Queues" {
    [Priority Queue] as PQueue
    [Simple Queue] as SQueue
    [Heap]
}

package "Internal" {
    [Internal Queue] as IQueue
}

' Relationships
Sched --> PQueue : Uses to manage tasks by priority
Nice --> Sched : Adjusts task priorities

PQueue --> Heap : Implemented using a binary heap
PQueue --> IQueue : Wraps internal queue logic

SQueue ..> IQueue : A simpler queue implementation

note right of Sched
  A scheduler that executes tasks
  based on their assigned priority.
end note

note left of PQueue
  A classic priority queue data structure.
end note

note bottom of Nice
  Provides a mechanism to manage
  "niceness" values, which can be
  mapped to priorities in the scheduler.
end note

@enduml
